Genitalia
. Pygophore brown, elongate setae generally scattered and with a dense brush posteriorly (Fig. 
44
). Parameres lacking. Phallosoma with basal oblique striations hidden behind pygophore; abrupt broadly rounded dextral gibbosity; gibbosity narrowing and continuing distad on right side; apex with rounded rim and opening to left, with longitudinally expansive, lightly sclerotized ventral flange (Fig. 
44
); sclerotized vesica distad of phallosoma.
